.TH SNEKMAP 1 "June 2026" "SnekMap 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
snekmap \- network reconnaissance and vulnerability assessment
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B snekmap
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I TARGET
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B SnekMap
is a command-line network scanner that combines nmap-based port and service
detection with automated CVE correlation, default credential testing,
protocol-specific misconfiguration checks, cross-finding correlation, and
multi-format report generation.
.PP
.I TARGET
may be a single IP address, a hostname, or a CIDR range
(e.g.\& \fB192.168.1.1\fR, \fBscanme.nmap.org\fR, \fB10.0.0.0/24\fR).
.PP
SnekMap runs in three stages after scanning:
.TP
\fBCVE correlation\fR
Per-port CVE lookup via the NIST NVD API v2.0.
Service detection confidence below 60% suppresses correlation entirely;
version confidence below 70% restricts matching to the major version only.
Results are cached locally at
.I ~/.snekmap/cve_cache.json
for 24 hours.
.TP
\fBCredential testing\fR
Common default credentials are tested against FTP (port 21), SSH (22),
MySQL (3306), and Redis (6379) when those ports are open.
.TP
\fBProtocol checks\fR
Active misconfiguration probes: LDAP anonymous binding (389), SMB null
sessions (139/445), DNS zone transfer AXFR (53), NFS world-accessible
exports (111/2049), and SNMP weak community strings (161).
.PP
A correlation pass then analyses the combined findings for patterns such
as Active Directory Domain Controller indicators, database-and-web-server
co-location (SQL injection escalation), and anomalous OS/service
combinations.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fast
Fast scan: top 100 ports only.
Faster on large networks but may miss non-standard service ports.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-deep
Deep scan: all 65535 ports.
Slow; best suited for focused single-host assessments.
These two flags are mutually exclusive.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cve
Skip CVE lookups.
Useful when working offline or when speed matters more than vulnerability data.
.TP
.BI \-\-export " FORMAT"
Export a report without the interactive menu.
.I FORMAT
is one of:
.BR html ", " pdf ", " json ", " csv ", " all .
.TP
.BI \-o " DIR" ", \-\-output\-dir " DIR
Directory in which to save report files.
Defaults to
.B ~/Desktop
if it exists, then
.BR ~/.snekmap/reports .
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress the banner and all progress spinners.
Useful when piping output or running from scripts.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the SnekMap version string and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a short usage summary and exit.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NVD_API_KEY
When set, authenticates requests to the NIST NVD API and raises the rate
limit from 5 to 50 requests per 30 seconds \(em roughly 10x faster CVE
lookups on targets with many open ports.
Request a free key at \fIhttps://nvd.nist.gov/developers/request-an-api-key\fR.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.snekmap/cve_cache.json
Disk-backed CVE result cache.
Entries expire after 24 hours.
Safe to delete; it will be recreated on the next scan.
.TP
.I ~/.snekmap/reports/
Default report output directory when
.B ~/Desktop
does not exist.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Standard scan of a single host:
.RS
.nf
snekmap 192.168.1.10
.fi
.RE
.TP
Fast scan of a /24 network:
.RS
.nf
snekmap 192.168.1.0/24 \-f
.fi
.RE
.TP
Deep scan with OS detection (requires root) and PDF export:
.RS
.nf
sudo snekmap 10.0.0.5 \-d \-\-export pdf
.fi
.RE
.TP
Offline scan — no CVE lookup, no internet needed:
.RS
.nf
snekmap 192.168.1.10 \-\-no\-cve
.fi
.RE
.TP
Quiet JSON export for automated pipelines:
.RS
.nf
snekmap 10.0.0.0/24 \-q \-\-export json \-o /tmp/scans
.fi
.RE
.
.SH NOTES
OS detection (\fB\-O\fR) is passed to nmap automatically and requires
root or Administrator privileges.
SnekMap falls back to a scan without OS detection when elevated privileges
are unavailable; all other features remain functional.
.PP
Protocol checks (LDAP, SMB, DNS, NFS, SNMP) require the corresponding
command-line tools (\fBldapsearch\fR, \fBsmbclient\fR, \fBdig\fR,
\fBshowmount\fR, \fBsnmpwalk\fR) to be installed.
Missing tools are silently skipped.
.PP
SSH and MySQL credential testing requires the optional Python packages
\fBparamiko\fR and \fBpymysql\fR respectively.
Uncomment the relevant lines in \fIrequirements.txt\fR and run
\fBpip install \-r requirements.txt\fR to enable them.
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nmap (1),
.BR curl (1),
.BR dig (1),
.BR smbclient (1),
.BR ldapsearch (1)
.
